    <description>
        <p><em>NymVPN</em> desktop application</p>
        <p>
            NymVPN is a decentralized, mixnet and zero-knowledge VPN.
            It provides the following features:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>5-hop <em>Anonymous</em> mode (using Nym <em>mixnet</em>)</li>
            <li>2-hop <em>Fast</em> mode (using <em>WireGuard</em>)</li>
            <li>No centralized logs</li>
            <li>Hide your public IP</li>
            <li>Entry and exit hop location</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            NOTE: this package only provides the <em>client</em> application.
            For the VPN to work, the <em>daemon</em> must be installed and running.
            You can install it from these separate packages:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>deb package (requires to setup the Nym deb repository): nym-vpnd</li>
            <li>AUR packages: nym-vpnd and nym-vpnd-bin</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For more details, please check https://nymvpn.com/en/download/linux</p>
        <p>
            Alternatively you can get the binary directly from the GitHub releases:
            Go to https://github.com/nymtech/nym-vpn-client/releases
            Find the latest release with tag <em>nym-vpn-core-v1.2.3</em> and
            download the linux binaries archive nym-vpn-core-v1.2.3_linux_x86_64.tar.gz
            Extract the archive and run `nym-vpnd` binary (make it executable).
            NOTE: the daemon requires root privileges to run, e.g. run it with `sudo`.
        </p>
    </description>
